# LifeQuest — Cursor Rules

## Project
Telegram Mini App RPG for personal growth. React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind + Supabase + OpenRouter AI.
NOT Next.js. NO server components. NO SSR. Pure client-side SPA that runs inside Telegram WebApp.

## Stack
- React 18 + Vite + TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS (dark theme only)
- Supabase JS client (browser only, @supabase/supabase-js)
- Framer Motion for animations
- React Router v6 for navigation
- OpenRouter API for AI (not OpenAI directly)

## TypeScript
- Always use TypeScript. No `any` types ever.
- Prefer interfaces over types for objects.
- Use functional components only. No class components.
- Use `function` keyword for components, not `const arrow`.
- Descriptive variable names: isLoading, hasError, canUseChat.

## Code style
- No semicolons.
- Early returns for error conditions — no deeply nested if/else.
- All async functions wrapped in try/catch.
- Favor simplicity over cleverness.
- Mobile-first always (Telegram Mini App = phone screen).

## Folder structure (strict)
```
src/
  lib/          ← ALL external calls go here only
    supabase.ts   ← Supabase client
    ai.ts         ← OpenRouter API functions
    access.ts     ← Plan-based feature gating
    referral.ts   ← Referral system
    auth.ts       ← Telegram WebApp auth
  pages/        ← Full page components
  components/   ← Reusable UI components
  types/        ← TypeScript interfaces
api/
  cron/         ← Vercel cron jobs
  bot/          ← Telegram bot webhook
```

NEVER put Supabase queries or fetch calls directly in components.
ALWAYS use functions from src/lib/ in components.

## Supabase
- Use @supabase/supabase-js browser client only (no SSR, no @supabase/ssr).
- Always handle errors: `const { data, error } = await supabase.from(...)`.
- Check error before using data.
- Use VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY from env (not NEXT_PUBLIC_).

## Design — ALWAYS dark theme
- Background: #0a0a14
- Cards/surfaces: #111122
- Borders: #1a1a2e
- Primary: #534AB7 (purple)
- Accent: #7F77DD
- Success: #1D9E75
- Warning: #EF9F27
- Text primary: #ffffff
- Text secondary: #aaaaaa
- Text muted: #555566
- NO white backgrounds. NO light mode. EVER.

## Tailwind
- Use Tailwind for all styling.
- Custom colors configured in tailwind.config: primary, accent, dark bg.
- Mobile-first: start with base styles, add sm:/md: for larger screens.
- Safe area padding for iPhone: pb-safe, pt-safe.

## Animations
- Use Framer Motion for: character reveal, XP gain popups, level up, page transitions.
- CSS transitions for: hover states, button presses, tab switches.
- Keep animations under 400ms for interactions, under 1500ms for reveals.

## LifeQuest domain — naming is strict
- AI mentor = "Архитектор" (never "AI", "bot", "assistant", "chatbot")
- The enemy = "Тень" (never "shadow enemy" or similar)
- Character stats: mind, body, spirit, resource (never "stats array" or generic names)
- Plans: 'trial' | 'free' | 'pro' (these exact strings, checked via access.ts)
- Spheres: 'mind' | 'body' | 'spirit' | 'resource'
- Quest ranks: 'F' | 'E' | 'D' | 'C' | 'B' | 'A' | 'S'
- Never call it "diary app" or "habit tracker" — it's an RPG

## Feature access — always use access.ts
```typescript
// CORRECT
const allowed = await canUse(userId, 'ai_chat')
if (!allowed) return <Paywall feature="ai_chat" />

// WRONG — never hardcode plan checks in components
if (user.plan === 'free') return <div>Upgrade</div>
```

## AI calls — always use ai.ts
```typescript
// CORRECT
import { askQuestion } from '@/lib/ai'
const stream = await askQuestion(entry, context)

// WRONG — never call OpenRouter directly in components
const res = await fetch('https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/...')
```

## Telegram Mini App
- Always check window.Telegram?.WebApp before using TG APIs.
- Use Telegram.WebApp.themeParams for colors when available.
- Bottom navigation must account for safe area (Telegram bottom bar).
- All modals and overlays must work within TG WebApp frame (no position:fixed full-screen).
- Test on mobile viewport (375px width minimum).

## Components
- Every page has a loading state and error state.
- Use skeleton loaders, not spinners where possible.
- Empty states have a message and a CTA action.
- Paywall component wraps any Pro-only feature.
- XP gain always shows floating animation (+50 XP, +3 Дух).

## When building a new page, always:
1. Check if any feature on this page needs canUse() gating
2. Add loading + error states for all async data
3. Use dark theme colors (no white/light backgrounds)
4. Make it work on 375px mobile width
5. Add safe area padding at bottom for Telegram

# LifeQuest — Agent & Subagent Rules

## Core principle
For ANY task longer than ~30 lines of code, break it into subtasks
and delegate each to a specialized subagent with a clear role.
Never try to do everything in one giant response.

## How to delegate
Before writing code, output a plan:
```
Task: [what user asked]
Subagents needed:
  1. [Role] → [specific output]
  2. [Role] → [specific output]
  ...
Starting with subagent 1...
```

---

## Subagent roles — use exactly these when relevant

### 🗄 DATABASE AGENT
Role: "You are a Supabase database expert."
Responsibilities:
- Write all SQL migrations and table definitions
- Design RLS policies
- Write Supabase query functions in src/lib/supabase.ts
- Optimize queries, add indexes
- NEVER touches UI or business logic
Output: SQL files + TypeScript functions in src/lib/

### 🤖 AI AGENT
Role: "You are an OpenRouter API integration expert."
Responsibilities:
- Write all functions in src/lib/ai.ts
- Design system prompts for Архитектор
- Handle streaming responses
- Implement fallback logic between models
- NEVER touches UI or database directly
Output: src/lib/ai.ts functions only

### 🎨 UI AGENT
Role: "You are a React UI expert building dark-themed Telegram Mini Apps."
Responsibilities:
- Build React components and pages
- Apply dark theme (#0a0a14 bg, #534AB7 primary)
- Make everything mobile-first (375px)
- Use Tailwind only, no inline styles except dynamic values
- NEVER writes business logic or API calls — imports from src/lib/ only
Output: src/components/ and src/pages/ files

### ✨ ANIMATION AGENT
Role: "You are a Framer Motion animation expert."
Responsibilities:
- Character reveal animation
- XP gain floating text (+50 XP)
- Level up celebration sequence
- Page transition animations
- Stat bar fill animations
- ONLY adds motion to existing components, doesn't create new ones
Output: animation variants and motion components

### 🔐 ACCESS AGENT
Role: "You are a feature-gating and monetization logic expert."
Responsibilities:
- Maintain src/lib/access.ts
- Implement canUse() checks for all features
- Build Paywall component
- Handle trial/free/pro plan transitions
- Write cron jobs for trial expiry
- NEVER touches UI design
Output: src/lib/access.ts + src/components/Paywall.tsx

### 📨 NOTIFICATION AGENT
Role: "You are a Telegram Bot API expert."
Responsibilities:
- Write all bot message functions
- Design notification texts in Архитектор voice
- Handle webhook routing
- Write cron job logic for degradation and insights
- NEVER touches frontend code
Output: api/bot/ and api/cron/ files

### 🔗 REFERRAL AGENT
Role: "You are a referral system and growth mechanics expert."
Responsibilities:
- Maintain src/lib/referral.ts
- Build /referral page
- Handle milestone rewards
- NEVER touches unrelated features
Output: src/lib/referral.ts + src/pages/ReferralPage.tsx

---

## Task routing — which agent handles what

| User asks for... | Primary agent | Secondary |
|---|---|---|
| New page (Dashboard, Journal, etc.) | UI AGENT | ACCESS AGENT |
| Database table or query | DATABASE AGENT | — |
| AI response / Архитектор message | AI AGENT | — |
| Animation / character reveal | ANIMATION AGENT | UI AGENT |
| Payment / plan logic | ACCESS AGENT | DATABASE AGENT |
| Bot message / notification | NOTIFICATION AGENT | — |
| Referral feature | REFERRAL AGENT | DATABASE AGENT |
| New feature end-to-end | All agents sequentially | — |

---

## Sequential build order for a new feature

When asked to build something end-to-end, always follow this order:
1. DATABASE AGENT — create/update tables, write query functions
2. AI AGENT — add AI functions if needed
3. ACCESS AGENT — add feature gating if needed
4. UI AGENT — build the page/component using lib/ functions
5. ANIMATION AGENT — add motion if the feature has visual moments
6. NOTIFICATION AGENT — add bot messages if the feature triggers notifications

Never skip steps. Never combine agents.

---

## Subagent prompt template

When starting a subagent task, begin with:

```
[SUBAGENT: {ROLE NAME}]
Context: LifeQuest Telegram Mini App RPG.
Stack: React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind + Supabase + OpenRouter.
Your job: {specific responsibility}
Input: {what you have}
Output: {exactly what file/function to produce}
Constraints: {what NOT to do}
---
```

Example:
```
[SUBAGENT: UI AGENT]
Context: LifeQuest Telegram Mini App RPG.
Stack: React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind + Supabase + OpenRouter.
Your job: Build the /journal/new page.
Input: journal_entries table exists. askQuestion() is in src/lib/ai.ts. canUse() is in src/lib/access.ts.
Output: src/pages/NewEntryPage.tsx — full working component.
Constraints: No API calls in component. No white backgrounds. Mobile-first 375px. Import everything from src/lib/.
---
```

---

## Quality checks after each subagent

After every subagent output, verify:
- [ ] TypeScript: no `any` types
- [ ] No direct fetch/supabase calls in UI components
- [ ] Dark theme colors used (#0a0a14, #111122, #534AB7)
- [ ] Loading and error states present
- [ ] Mobile viewport compatible
- [ ] Naming matches domain (Архитектор not "AI", mind/body/spirit/resource)

If check fails → fix before moving to next subagent.

---

## Don'ts
- Never write a 200-line component in one shot without subagents
- Never let UI agent touch database
- Never let database agent design UI
- Never skip the sequential build order
- Never merge two agent roles into one ("UI + database agent") — they stay separate

## Hooks — always use, never rewrite

All data fetching hooks are in src/hooks/useLifeQuest.ts.
ALWAYS import from there. NEVER write useEffect+supabase directly in components.

Available hooks:
- useTelegramUser()        → current user auth
- useCharacter(userId)     → character data, gainXP(), revealCharacter()
- useXPProgress(xp, level) → progress bar percentage, xpToNext
- useJournal(userId)       → entries, addEntry(), isFirstEntry, monthlyCount
- useHabits(userId)        → habits, toggleHabit(), addHabit(), weekProgress
- useQuests(userId)        → quests, completeQuest(), activeCount
- usePlan(userId)          → isTrialActive, isPro, isFree, daysLeft
- useFeatureAccess(userId, feature) → boolean, use before any gated action
- useReferral(userId)      → referral stats
- useDegradationWarning(lastActive) → stage 0-4, warning text
- useFloatingXP()          → show(amount, label) for XP animations
- useTelegramTheme()       → haptic.success(), haptic.error(), expand()
- useCountUp(target)       → animated number counter
- useDebounce(value)       → debounced input value

When building any page: first line of component = import needed hooks.
